Four people were on Friday evening killed after a vehicle they were travelling in was involved in an accident on Friday evening.  Gilgil Sub County Police Commander John Onditi confirmed the four died at Soysambu Conservancy near Gilgil on the Nakuru-Nairobi Highway.  "Our preliminary findings indicate that four people who were travelling in a saloon car have died in the crash that also involved a trailer. The scene is still being processed," said Onditi.  The police boss said the accident has caused a heavy traffic jam along the major highway.  Gospel artiste, Marakwet Daughter, detained in hospital over Sh115,000 bill  Man jailed for five years for causing death of boy by dangerous driving  Artiste, 'Marakwet Daughter', cheats death in road crash  Thika Road accident leaves two police offices injured "We are appealing to motorists to be patient as we process the scene. Overlapping is likely to worsen the current gridlock," said Onditi.     Take a quick survey and help us improve our website!  Nine killed in dawn accident in Soysambu, Gilgil in head-on collision between matatu and trailer  Ajali Soysambu Gilgil: Watu 9 wamefariki mapema leo baada ya kuhusika kwenye ajali mbaya Gilgil  Gilgil Accident: PSV van crashes head on with a trailer, 9 reported dead with several others injured By Stephen Rutto and Irissheel Shanzu | 1 day ago By Robert Kiplagat  | 1 day ago By Antony Gitonga | 1 day ago By Kennedy Gachuhi | 2 days ago Read The Standard uninterrupted with no advertisements